{{About|the 2017 video game|the 1992 video game|Dreadnoughts (video game)|the board game|Dreadnought (naval wargame)}} {{Infobox video game | title = Dreadnought | image = Dreadnought video game logo 2017.png | developer = {{Unbulleted list|[[Six Foot]]|[[Yager Development]]}} | publisher = [[Grey Box (company)|Grey Box]] | engine = [[Unreal Engine 4]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/e3-2014-spec-ops-the-line-developer-reveals-new-game-dreadnought/1100-6420269/|title=E3 2014: Spec Ops: The Line Developer Reveals New Game, Dreadnought|last1=Newhouse|first1=Alex|publisher=[[GameSpot]]|date=10 June 2014|accessdate=20 November 2014}}</ref> | platforms = {{Unbulleted list|[[PlayStation 4]]|[[Microsoft Windows]]}} | released = {{Unbulleted list|'''PlayStation 4'''|5 December 2017|'''Microsoft Windows'''|14 October 2018}} | genre = [[Combat flight simulation]] | modes = [[Multiplayer]] }}
'''''Dreadnought''''' is a [[combat flight simulation game]] developed by [[Six Foot]] and [[Yager Development]], and published by [[Grey Box (company)|Grey Box]]. Following a closed beta phase, the game was released for [[PlayStation 4]] in December 2017, followed by a release for [[Microsoft Windows]] in October 2018.
== Gameplay == The player is the captain of a large spacecraft and uses projectile weapons to attack. The player is able to choose between several classes of ships, each with drawbacks and advantages in categories like speed and size. The ships are massive and are intended to give the feel of being a commander, not a rogue bounty hunter. As a result, gameplay involves large amounts of strategy and positioning. In addition to positioning the ship and choosing targets, the player may also allocate power to various parts of the ship. These areas include shields, weapons and engines.<ref name="PC_Gamer_E3_Preview">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/previews/dreadnought-e3-preview/|title=Dreadnought E3 Preview|last1=Butterworth|first1=Scott|publisher=[[PC Gamer]]|date=15 June 2014|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>
=== Multiplayer === In multiplayer, coordinated attacks and focus fire are important. Other players may choose to heal a damaged teammate. Matches last around ten minutes and players may switch ship classes after death depending on the match type.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2014/06/12/dreadnought-goes-big-with-huge-ships.aspx|title=Dreadnought Goes Big with Huge Ships|last1=Tack|first1=Daniel|publisher=[[Game Informer]]|date=12 June 2014|accessdate=5 September 2014}}</ref>
== Reception == Around the release of the steam version, co-developer Six Foot laid off 45 staff, approximately a third of its workforce.<ref name="layoffs">https://www.gameinformer.com/2018/10/18/layoffs-at-dreadnought-developer-six-foot</ref> Those affected were given the choice to either terminate their contracts or take an unpaid leave as long as the company struggled financially.<ref name="layoffs" />
