{{Infobox video game | title = Hlava Kasandry | image = Hlava Kasandry Cover.jpg | developer = LetDisk | publisher = | series = | designer = | composer = | engine = | platforms = Atari ST | released = 1993 | genre = Adventure, RPG, simulator }}
'''''Hlava Kasandry''''' (English: ''Cassandra's Head'') is a 1993 Czech video game, developed by Marek Nepožitek's company LetDisk and based on the Polish novel [[Głow Kasandra]]. It was released on the Atari ST but is compatible with Atari TT and Atari Falcon.
==Production== The creators of the game worked in their free time. The development was influenced by the inexperience of developers who had to learn a lot of things during their work on the game. They included a number of features that they retrospectively deemed unnecessary. The game was then tested by friends of the game authors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://letdisk.wordpress.com/2014/11/06/realizace/|title=Realizace|date=6 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref> Piracy was a major issue at the time of the game. The authors therefore gave particular focus to copy protection. They had experience of copying games themselves, and therefore decided to create a particularly effective protection to prevent pirates from cracking the game. Unfortunately, this protection made it impossible to create physical copies or floppy images for use in emulators.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://letdisk.wordpress.com/2014/11/06/ochrana-proti-kopirovani/|title=Ochrana proti kopírování|date=6 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref>
In 2004, Marek Nepožitek, then a co-founder of Cinemax, decided to re-release ''Hlava Kasandry'', whose play on various platforms had previously been prevented by anti-piracy protection. He had to work around this, and did not find a solution until 2014; a free version for emulators was released in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://letdisk.wordpress.com/2014/11/06/zachrana-projektu/|title=Záchrana projektu|date=6 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atariportal.cz/news_detail.php?itmid=2001006|title=Česko-slovenský Atari portál: Hlava Kasandry - aktualizace|first=cs.atari.org|last=team|website=www.atariportal.cz}}</ref>
==Plot and gameplay== The game is set for the future, when a handful of people have to survive in a world destroyed by a massive nuclear conflict. The game follows the story of Teodor Hornice, who deals with the destruction of dangerous warheads. He must destroy a rocket name Kassandra that could destroy the planet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldgames.sk/mag/score-10/page/51/|title=Hlava Kasandry|last=Kment|first=Štěpán "Dawn"|date=1994|website=Score|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldgames.sk/mag/excalibur-24/page/13/|title=Hlava Kasandry|last=Chlebek|first=Jan "Ted Johnson"|date=1994|website=Excalibur|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
The game is a mix of adventure, RPG and simulator. It is played with a joystick and a mouse. While players search for the missing rocket, they must pay attention to fuel and life while avoiding rasioactive areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hernisnob.cz/2010/05/hlava-kasandry.html|title=Hlava Kasandry|website=www.hernisnob.cz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://letdisk.wordpress.com/2014/11/06/hlava-kasandry/|title=Hlava Kasandry|date=6 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref>
==Critical reception== At the time of release, the game was accepted by the reviewers. The game received a rating of 76% from Narsil and 71% from Excalibur.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldgames.sk/mag/narsil-5/page/4/|title=Hlava Kasandry|last=Rous|first=Karel "Empty Head"|date=1994|website=Narsil|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldgames.sk/mag/excalibur-34/page/30/|title=Hlava Kasandry|last=Kment|first=Štěpán "Dawn"|date=1994|website=Excalibur|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
