This is a list of films in which the theme of [[socialism]] features prominently in the movie.
*[[Capitalism: A Love Story]]- 2009 - by American film maker [[Michael Moore]]. A documentary exploring and criticizing capitalism in America. *[[Che (2008 film)|Che]] - 2008- is a two part biopic about the socialist revolutionary [[Ernesto "Che" Guevara]]. *[[Sicko]]- 2007 - by American film maker [[Michael Moore]]. A documentary investigating health care in the United States and how it compares with socialized public health services. *''[[Lights in the Dusk]]'' by [[Aki Kaurismäki]] ([[2006 in film|2006]]). It has been argued that films deals with the ways in which "[c]apitalism has painted the town red, just a different shade of red from its socialist connotations" as well as that "rock is so important to the director that a number of his males, including Koistinen, favor a 50s, greasy, sweptback hair style, to go along with their love of rock 'n' roll (definitely a reminder of how rock was the way to rebel in socialist countries)."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.austinfilm.org/page.aspx?pid=3277 |title=''Lights in the Dusk'' (''Laitakaupungin valot''): Written, Produced, Directed, and Edited by Aki Kaurismäki |last=Nafus |first=Chale, Director of Programming, [[Austin Film Society]] |publisher=[[Austin Film Society]] |access-date=8 July 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708221342/http://www.austinfilm.org/page.aspx?pid=3277 |archivedate=8 July 2015 |df= }}</ref> *[[The Wind That Shakes The Barley (film)]] - 2006 - A film set during the [[Irish War of Independence]] and [[Irish Civil War]]. The film shows the divergences in the Irish republican movement during the revolutionary period and the civil war. *[[Reds (film)|''Reds'']]- 1981- Film about the life and career of [[John Reed (journalist)|John Reed]], particularly his time in [[Petrograd]] which formed the basis of his book, [[Ten Days That Shook the World]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/dec/19/100-best-nonfiction-books-no-47-ten-days-that-shook-world-john-reed-review|title=The 100 best nonfiction books: No 47 – Ten Days That Shook the World by John Reed (1919)|last=McCrum|first=Robert|date=2016-12-19|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=2017-02-15|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> * [[Winstanley (film)|Winstanley]] - 1975 - A film about [[Gerrard Winstanley]] who along with the group known as the [[Diggers]] carried out one of the worlds first socialist living experiments. The film reflects class antagonism between peasants and lords in a feudal economy. * ''[[The Working Class Goes to Heaven]]'' - 1971 - Italian film<ref name="http://linchpin.ca/Blogs/Film-Review-Working-Class-Go-Heaven">[http://linchpin.ca/Blogs/Film-Review-Working-Class-Go-Heaven Film Review, http://linchpin.ca/Blogs/Film-Review-Working-Class-Go-Heaven] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130509194106/http://linchpin.ca/Blogs/Film-Review-Working-Class-Go-Heaven |date=2013-05-09 }}</ref> * ''[[Modern Times (film)|Modern Times]]'' - 1936 - The film references the struggle of the working classes during the Great Depression; long working hours, little job security and meager salary, while the upper classes remain wealthy and bide their time. A tale of struggle of a working couple.<ref name="imdb review of Modern Times">[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0027977/reviews imdb review of Modern Times]</ref> * [[October: Ten Days That Shook the World]]- 1928 - A [[Soviet Union]] film by [[Sergei Eisenstein]] which presents a dramatic retelling of the Russian revolution in 1917 which marked the beginnings of the soviet union. *''[[Strike (1925 film)|Strike]]'' - 1925 - A [[Soviet Union]] film by [[Sergei Eisenstein]].<ref name="imdb review of Strike">[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0015361/, imdb review of Strike]</ref> *''[[Battleship Potemkin]]'' - 1925 Eisenstein film covering one of the formative events of the Russian revolution, the mutiny of a ship's crew against their officers.<ref name="Taylor2001">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iecBAwAAQBAJ|title=Battleship Potemkin: The Film Companion|date=12 January 2001|publisher=I.B.Tauris|isbn=978-0-85771-073-4|author=Richard Taylor}}</ref>
