{{Other uses|Critics' Circle (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox organization |name=Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle |founded=1969 |founders= |location=[[United States]] |headquarters=[[Los Angeles]], [[California]] |type=[[Theatre|Theatrical criticism]] }}
The '''Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle''' (LADCC) is an organization located in [[Los Angeles, California]], dedicated to excellence in [[theatre|theatrical]] [[criticism]], and to the encouragement and improvement of theatre in the [[Greater Los Angeles Area]].<ref name=LAT>{{cite news|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url=http://touch.latimes.com/#section/-1/article/p2p-85725799/|title=L.A. Drama Critics Circle Awards: LGBT Center's 'Hit the Wall' leads nominenter.|first=Jessica|last=Gelt|date=January 29, 2016|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref>
Founded in 1969, the LADCC presents the annual [[Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle Award]].
