{{for|the football team|Nagaworld FC}} [[File:NagaWorld (Phnom Penh).jpg|thumb|right|NagaWorld, [[Phnom Penh]]]] '''NagaCorp Ltd.''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: 金界控股有限公司) ({{SEHK|3918}}) is the largest hotel, gaming, and leisure operator in [[Cambodia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/muhammadcohen/2014/06/15/nagacorp-makes-casino-holiday-in-cambodia-no-joke/#665fa30642f9|title=NagaCorp Makes Casino 'Holiday In Cambodia' No Joke|website=Forbes|access-date=2016-03-29}}</ref> Its property, '''NagaWorld''', is Phnom Penh's only integrated hotel-casino entertainment complex. NagaCorp holds a 70-year casino licence in Cambodia which runs until 2065,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ggrasia.com/nagacorp-reassures-investors-over-cambodia-licence/|title=GGRAsia – NagaCorp reassures investors over Cambodia licence|website=www.ggrasia.com|access-date=2016-03-29}}</ref> and has a monopoly within a {{convert|200|km|adj=on}} radius of [[Phnom Penh]] (except the Cambodia-Vietnam border area, [[Bokor Hill Station|Bokor]], [[Kirirom National Park|Kirirom Mountains]], and [[Sihanoukville (city)|Sihanoukville]]) until 2035.
The Naga casino first opened on May 1, 1995 on a boat moored in the [[Mekong River]] in Phnom Penh.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cambodia opens floating casino|newspaper=UPI|author=Tricia Fitzgerald|date=May 1, 1995|url=https://www.upi.com/Archives/1995/05/01/Cambodia-opens-floating-casino/8045799300800/|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref><ref name=rollet>{{cite news|title=NagaWorld celebrates 20 eventful years at the table|newspaper=Phnom Penh Post|author=Charles Rollet|date=May 15, 2015|url=https://www.phnompenhpost.com/post-weekend/nagaworld-celebrates-20-eventful-years-table|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref> The casino moved to its current land-based facility in 2003.<ref name=rollet /><ref>{{cite news|title=Naga Casino moves to riverfront complex|newspaper=The Cambodia Daily|author=Kate Woodsome|date=September 26, 2003|url=https://www.cambodiadaily.com/news/naga-casino-moves-to-riverfront-complex-41376/|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref> NagaCorp held its [[initial public offering]] on the [[Hong Kong Stock Exchange]] in 2006, making it the first gaming-related company to trade on the exchange, and the first company with operations in Cambodia to become publicly traded.<ref>{{cite news|title=NagaCorp raises HK$715m from IPO|newspaper=South China Morning Post|date=October 13, 2006|url=http://www.scmp.com/node/567468|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NagaCorp Ltd.|publisher=NagaWorld|url=http://www.nagaworld.com/nagacorp-ltd/|accessdate=2018-05-26}}</ref>
