The '''Stralsund Theatre''' ('''{{lang-de|Stralsunder Theater}}''') in the German town of [[Stralsund]] has a long tradition. Performances of theatre pieces on the ''[[Alter Markt (Stralsund)|Alter Markt]]'' are documented in the years 1553 (''"Tragedie van deme Daniel"'') and 1584 (''"De Tragedien van Susannen"''). The present building was designed by [[Carl Moritz (architect)|Carl Moritz]] and opened in 1914. The tradition has continued since the merger of the  theatres of the towns of Stralsund and Greifswald in 1994 into the [[Theatre of West Pomerania]] (''{{lang|de|Theater Vorpommern}}'').

