[[Image:ColbertDVD.jpg|200px|thumb|right|The cover of ''The Best of The Colbert Report''.]]
'''''The Best of the Colbert Report''''' is a single-disc DVD compiling memorable segments from ''[[The Colbert Report]]'''s [[List of The Colbert Report episodes (2005)|2005]], [[List of The Colbert Report episodes (2006)|2006]], and [[List of The Colbert Report episodes (2007)|2007]] seasons. It was released by [[Comedy Central]] on November 6, 2007.

The compilation features a number of [[Better Know a District]] segments in which Colbert interviews members of Congress, including [[Eleanor Holmes Norton]] and [[Robert Wexler]].  Clips from [[Recurring segments on The Colbert Report#The W.C3.B8rd|The Wørd]] are also included, such as [[Truthiness]] and [[Wikipedia in culture#Wikiality|Wikiality]], and some of Colbert's better-known interviews, such as [[Bill O'Reilly (commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]], [[Willie Nelson]], [[Jane Fonda]] and [[Gloria Steinem]].  Other segments featured include [[Recurring Segments on The Colbert Report#Tip of the Hat, Wag of the Finger|Tip of the Hat, Wag of the Finger]], [[Recurring Segments on The Colbert Report#The Threatdown|The ThreatDown]], Colbert's "Green Screen Challenge" and subsequent [[lightsaber]] battle with [[George Lucas]] and the "Meta-Free-Phor-All" with [[Sean Penn]].<ref name="TV Squad">Wu, Annie (October 28, 2007). [http://www.tvsquad.com/2007/10/28/the-best-of-the-colbert-report-dvd-review/ The Best of the Colbert Report - DVD review]. ''TV Squad''. Accessed on 2007-12-01.</ref><ref name="Blogcritics">Creech, Anna (November 11, 2007). [http://blogcritics.org/archives/2007/11/11/225540.php DVD Review: The Best of the Colbert Report] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071215050747/http://blogcritics.org/archives/2007/11/11/225540.php |date=December 15, 2007 }}. ''Blogcritics''. Accessed on 2007-12-01.</ref>

Copies of the DVD sold at [[Best Buy]] included a bonus disc, which contained the entire first season of ''[[Tek Jansen|Stephen Colbert Presents: Stephen Colbert's Alpha Squad 7: The New Tek Jansen Adventures]]''.<ref>[http://www.nofactzone.net/?p=2599 A word on the "Best of The Colbert Report" bonus disc]. ''No Fact Zone.'' Accessed on 2007-12-01.</ref>

DVD reviews were mixed, with some critics praising the selection of clips,<ref name="Blogcritics" /> while others suggested that the segments featured in the compilation represented the most well-known stunts as opposed to the "best".<ref name="TV Squad" />  Many were critical of the amount of material on the DVD, which contains 175 minutes of clips from the show, but no bonus features.<ref>Arseneau, Adam (December 5, 2007). [http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/bestcolbertreport.php DVD Verdict Review - The Best of the Colbert Report] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071214174220/http://www.dvdverdict.com/reviews/bestcolbertreport.php |date=December 14, 2007 }}. ''DVD Verdict''. Accessed on 2007-12-23.</ref>

